# Python & FastAPI

- Python 3.12; type-hint public APIs; prefer async I/O (`async def` + `httpx`/`asyncpg`).
- Pydantic v2 schemas for request/response — they drive OpenAPI tags accurately.
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 async style; Alembic for migrations; no raw business SQL in routes.
- Routes stay thin: validate → call service → map errors to envelope `{error_code, message, request_id}`.
- Providers implement Protocols; construct only via `ProviderManager` / DI.
- Tests: `pytest` + `pytest-asyncio`; one focused test module per domain concern.
- Logging: structured JSON; scrub secrets; include `request_id` when in request scope.
- Avoid `print()` in app code; avoid blocking calls on the event loop.
